---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const services = [
  {
    cat: "For everybody",
    name: "See People Clearly",
    body: "Your team learns about themselves, each other, and a language that makes important things easier and safe to say. Most companies start here.",
    href: "/professional-work/see-people-clearly",
    sig: "#006073",
    wash: "#AAC1CB",
  },
  {
    cat: "For leadership",
    name: "Manage With Meaning",
    body: "Your managers already know how to manage the work. This is how they manage the people doing it.",
    href: "/professional-work/manage-with-meaning",
    sig: "#9C1B30",
    wash: "#E7B9B0",
  },
  {
    cat: "Built for you",
    name: "Team Effectiveness",
    body: "Not a stock curriculum. Built around what your team is actually working through.",
    href: "/professional-work/team-effectiveness",
    sig: "#D57A27",
    wash: "#F2D5B3",
  },
  {
    cat: "Confidential",
    name: "Workplace Support",
    body: "Confidential, neutral help for the people situations a manager shouldn't have to carry alone.",
    href: "/professional-work/workplace-support",
    sig: "#2BA1A3",
    wash: "#CCD8DE",
  },
  {
    cat: "Ongoing",
    name: "On Retainer",
    body: "Everything above, on a standing basis, shaped to your company.",
    href: "/professional-work/on-retainer",
    sig: "#EF9C20",
    wash: "#FCE9CD",
  },
];

// Client logos as one-color Teal marks. M Squared, South Valley Family Dental,
// and Welch Music render as typographic marks until logo art is supplied.
const logos = [
  { src: "/img/logos/modern-expo-teal.png", alt: "Modern Expo and Events" },
  { src: "/img/logos/small-satellite-conference-teal.png", alt: "Small Satellite Conference" },
  { src: "/img/logos/plan-to-eat-teal.png", alt: "Plan to Eat" },
  { src: "/img/logos/hlo-lighting-teal.png", alt: "HLO Lighting" },
  { src: "/img/logos/power-driven-diesel-teal.png", alt: "Power Driven Diesel" },
  { src: "/img/logos/total-tree-care-teal.png", alt: "Total Tree Care" },
];
---

<Base
  title="Professional Work · Ennea Evolution"
  description="There's no such thing as just business. Enneagram workshops, manager development, team effectiveness, workplace support, and ongoing partnerships for the people part of your company."
>
  <!-- SECTION 1 · white · hero, three lines, given room -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow" style="--accent:var(--teal);">Professional Work</p>
      <h1>There's no such thing as <em class="mk-underline">just</em> business.</h1>
      <p class="lead">There's only life, and a good share of it happens at work, in the company you keep.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 2 · white · opening, logos, Salinda callout -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p>Many of the companies I work with have jobs that don't let up. Events, medical, tech. Deadlines that don't move, customers who need you now, and good people running hard. When the work is like that, the people part is the first thing to get skipped. It's usually the thing that would have helped most.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="container" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
      <div class="logo-row">
        {logos.map((l) => <img src={l.src} alt={l.alt} />)}
        <span class="logo-text">M Squared</span>
        <span class="logo-text">South Valley Family Dental</span>
        <span class="logo-text">Welch Music</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container narrow" style="margin-top:2.75rem;">
      <blockquote class="pullquote testimonial" style="--accent:var(--teal); margin-inline:auto;">
        "My team has been buzzing all week. Leadership is even talking about scheduling an additional training for the retail team and the floral team. They also are interested in doing a training just for them as senior executive leadership and ownership. We love what you have brought to Modern."
        <cite>Salinda, Vice President, Modern Expo</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 3 · white · what it's for, two columns -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">What it's for</h3>
      <div class="copy-split">
        <div>
          <h4>The hard stuff</h4>
          <ul class="recognition-rows" style="--dot:#9C1B30;">
            <li>A manager who is carrying everyone, and won't stop.</li>
            <li>Someone you promoted because she was your best, now struggling at something nobody ever taught her.</li>
            <li>Two people twenty years apart who both want to do good work and can't see the other one doing it.</li>
            <li>Everyone is working hard, something is draining, and you can't find where.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="vsep" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div>
          <h4>The good stuff</h4>
          <ul class="recognition-rows" style="--dot:#2BA1A3;">
            <li>Your team works well and you're about to grow. You'd like to keep what you built.</li>
            <li>Nothing is wrong. You just don't think a good team stays good on its own.</li>
            <li>You want to hand your people a genuinely good day, and have it still matter a month later.</li>
            <li>There's a little friction you'd rather deal with now than wait for it to turn into a big fix.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="center" style="max-width:62ch; margin:2.5rem auto 0;">You don't need a problem to do this. If you have one, we'll do that work, and we'll do it well. Every workplace benefits from an investment in its people, and whether we're fixing or building, we'll do work that works.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 4 · white · callout bar -->
  <section class="panel" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container narrow center">
      <blockquote class="pullquote" style="--accent:var(--teal); margin-inline:auto;">Fixing is seeing what's wrong. Building is seeing what's possible. We'll do a bit of both. And we'll use the Enneagram to do it.</blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 5 · white · how we can work together, five cards -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">How we can work together</h3>
      <div class="services-grid">
        {services.map((s) => (
          <a href={s.href} class="card washes" style={`--rule:${s.sig}; --wash:${s.wash};`}>
            <p class="card-cat">{s.cat}</p>
            <p class="card-title" style="font-size:1.12rem;">{s.name}</p>
            <p style="margin-bottom:0;">{s.body}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="center" style="max-width:56ch; margin:2.5rem auto 0;">Every company starts somewhere different. Pick the one that fits what you're after, and we'll build from there.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 6 · white · about on retainer, expanded -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>About On Retainer</h3>
      <p>Some companies don't want a workshop. They want somebody who knows them.</p>
      <p>On retainer, I become a standing part of how your company takes care of its people. It looks different everywhere. Sometimes it's quarterly workshops, planned with you around what your company actually needs that quarter. Sometimes it's a set number of confidential sessions a month that anyone in the company can sign up for, so your people have somewhere to take the hard thing. Sometimes it's building a culture from scratch and staying long enough to see it through. Often it's a mix, and it changes as you do.</p>
      <p>What you're really getting is a thought partner who knows your business and your people, and who brings a skill set most companies can't justify carrying full time. You get the benefit without the salary.</p>
      <p>By the end of a year, this isn't a workshop your company attended. It's how your company talks.</p>
      <a href="/professional-work/on-retainer" class="arrow-link" style="--accent:var(--teal);">More about working on retainer →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 7 · white · how it works, two columns -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">How it works</h3>
      <div class="copy-split">
        <div>
          <h4>The Enneagram</h4>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0;">I use the Enneagram. It's a personality assessment, and one people love taking, because it finally explains the thing everyone is quietly curious about, which is why they're the way they are. It maps what a person is reaching for, what they're protecting, what motivates them, and what wears them out. Knowing your type on its own is a fun fact. What we do with it is the part that matters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="vsep" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div>
          <h4>And beyond</h4>
          <p style="margin-bottom:0;">Then we apply it to the actual work. How to run a meeting people get something out of. How to match the task to the person who should have it. When to push for the result and when to pull back and let people regroup. What actually motivates each person on your team, which is almost never the same thing. Every one of those gets taught through the Enneagram, so it stops being general advice and becomes instructions for the specific person in front of you. Not give better feedback. How to give her the feedback she needs, in a one-on-one, when you already know she's stretched thin.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="center" style="max-width:66ch; margin:2.5rem auto 0;">People come in expecting a training day and leave having actually talked to each other. There's a lot of laughing. There's also a fair amount of someone going quiet for a second because they just understood something about a person they've sat next to for six years. Both of those are the point. The fun isn't decoration. It's what makes people honest enough for the rest of it to work.</p>
      <blockquote class="pullquote testimonial" style="--accent:var(--teal); margin:2rem auto 0;">
        "I came in thinking this would be another personality thing. It wasn't. I'm easily still using the concepts and language because it makes sense and actually works."
        <cite>Grant, owner, M Squared</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 8 · white · why me -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>Why me</h3>
      <p>Half my week is one-on-one with people, up close, under real pressure. So none of this is theory. I watch how people really operate, then bring it into your building.</p>
      <p>And I've sat where you're sitting. My husband and I have started, run, and sold businesses of our own. I know what it costs when the people part goes wrong, and I know what it feels like to make payroll.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- SECTION 9 · white · bring this to your team -->
  <section class="panel center">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>Bring this to your team</h3>
      <p>Tell me about your team, whether something's getting in the way or you just want to invest in them. I'll tell you whether I can help and what it would look like.</p>
      <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Let's Talk</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* proof-panel logo row: one-color Teal marks, optically even, wraps to two lines */
  .logo-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2.4vw, 2rem);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .logo-row img { height: 28px; width: auto; }
  .logo-text {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    color: var(--teal);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* five service cards: flexible grid, five across on wide screens */
  .services-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(190px, 1fr));
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
  }

  /* two-column copy sections with a short vertical gold hairline between */
  .copy-split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .copy-split .vsep { width: 1px; background: var(--gold); align-self: stretch; }
  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .copy-split { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .copy-split .vsep { width: 80px; height: 1px; justify-self: center; margin-block: 0.5rem; }
  }
</style>
